Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- Android `OnPause` maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event (lost focus but may still be visible); `OnStop` maps to `Stopped` (fully backgrounded).
- iOS `DidEnterBackground` maps to `Stopped`.
- If you don't need platform-specific APIs, you can use the simpler cross-platform approach — override `OnStopped()` on a `Window` subclass, which fires on both platforms when backgrounded.

**Cross-platform alternative:**

```csharp
public class AppWindow : Window
{
    public AppWindow(Page page) : base(page) { }

    protected override void OnStopped()
    {
        base.OnStopped();
        // Runs on background for both Android (OnStop) and iOS (DidEnterBackground)
    }
}
```

⚠️ Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
